value.value: An exposure involving growth during the rabi crop season (October-March) as practiced in South Asia.
An exposure involving growth during the kharif crop season (May-October) as practised in South Asia.
An exposure involving growth during the winter season.
An exposure involving growth during the summer season.
An exposure involving growth during the spring season.
An exposure involving growth during the autumn season.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the use of antibiotic for selection purposes.
An exposure involving growth in the presence of non-mineral nutrients to study various types of responses.
An inorganic chemical exposure (PECO:0001004) involving the application of a mineral or a combination of minerals.
A plant macronutrient exposure (PECO:0007240)  involving the use of the primary plant macronutrients nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P), and potassium (K).

definition.value: These plant macronutrients are required by the plant in greatest quantities for normal growth.

value.value: An exposure involving the use of macronutrients (Ca, Mg, S) as supplement to study various types of responses. These macronutrients are used less often as fertilizers than the primary elements.
An exposure involving the exposure of plant to elemental forms of nutrients as supplement. These are not considered essential elements.
A salt exposure (PECO:0007185) involving the use of sodium chloride salt as supplement to liquid and soil growth media to study various types of responses on its application.
An exposure involving growing plants in soil growth media with varying contents.
An exposure involving growing plants in varying textures of soil growth media.
An exposure involving growing plants in a sandy soil growth media.
An exposure involving growing plants in a growth media containing organic matter.
An exposure involving growing plants in a silty soil growth media.
An exposure involving growing plants in a clay soil growth media.
An exposure involving the growth of a plant with the pathogen Cochliobolus spp.
An exposure involving growing plants in soil growth media of varying pH levels.
An exposure involving growing plants in acidic (low pH) soil growth media.
A plant fungal exposure (PECO:0007233) involving the exposure of plant to the pathogen Sphaerulina oryzina.

definition.value: Sphaerulina oryzina is a causal agent for rice Narrow Brown Leaf Spot disease.

value.value: An exposure involving growth of a plant in the geographical region of the Earth limited in latitude by the two tropics, the Tropic of Cancer and the Tropic of Capricorn, and thus centered on the equator.

definition.value: This area lies approximately between 23.5 N latitude and 23.5 S latitude, and includes all the parts of the Earth where the sun reaches a point directly overhead at least once during the solar year (north of the Tropic of Cancer and south of the Tropic of Capricorn the sun never reaches an azimuth of 90 or directly overhead).

value.value: An exposure involving growing plants in basic (high pH) soil growth media.
A herbicide exposure (PECO:0007183) involving the use of diuron (DCMU).

definition.value: Diuron blocks the reduction of plastoquinone in the photosynthetic light reaction and keeps the plastoquinone pool oxidized.

value.value: A plant exposure (PECO:0001001) involving exposure to the various factors that comprise a geographical/regional location.
An exposure involving the growth of a plant with the pathogen Entyloma oryzae. It is a causal agent for rice Leaf Smut disease.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of cytokinin (or its homolog) growth hormone.
A plant growth medium exposure (PECO:0007147) involving growing plants in liquid growth media.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of ethylene (or its homolog) growth hormone.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of GA (or its homolog) growth hormone.
An auxin exposure (PECO:0007074) involving the use of IAA (or its homolog) growth hormone.
An exposure involving liquid growth medium for cell cultured samples.

An exposure involving the growth of a plant with the pathogen Microdochium oryzae. It is a causal agent for rice various forms of Leaf scald disease such as Brown Leaf Blight Disease , Leaf Sheath Browning Disease, Leaf Tip Blight Disease and Leaf Tip Dying Disease.
A fungal plant exposure (PECO:0007233) involving the exposure of plant to the pathogen belonging to Basidiomycetes class.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of auxin (or its homolog).
Treatment involving the exposure of plant to the pathogen Tilletia barclayana. It is a causal agent for rice Kernel Smut disease.

In biological experiments often it refer to the length of the exposure time. The treatment also includes the quantity of light falling on a per unit area. This may be expressed either in terms of hours for which teh radiation was available or in the units of luminous flux or the lumens.
Treatment involving the use of sulfate fertilizer and its components as supplements to study various types of responses.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of JA (or its homolog).
Treatment involving the exposure of plant to the pathogen Phoma sorghina.

definition.value: It is a causal agent for rice Glume Blight Disease.

value.value: Treatment involving the exposure of plant to the pests that do not falll under the well known classes of birds, mammals, insects, nematode and molluscs.
A plant nutrient exposure (PECO:0007241) involving the use of a fertilizer, a combination of plant nutrients.
Treatment involving the use of inorganic fertilizer and its components as supplements to study various types of responses.
Treatment involving the use of organic fertilizer and its component as supplements to study various types of responses.
